{"id":"project-LICHEN-ocau","title":"coap_msg.c: strtoul error checking incomplete","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_msg.c
Lines: 577-584

Message ID parsing from URI path uses strtoul:
```c
char *endptr;
unsigned long val = strtoul(id_buf, &endptr, 10);

if (*endptr != '\0' || val > UINT32_MAX) {
    return coap_respond(..., COAP_RESPONSE_CODE_NOT_FOUND, ...);
}
msg_id = (uint32_t)val;
```

Missing checks:
1. strtoul sets errno on overflow but errno is not checked
2. If id_buf is empty string, strtoul returns 0 with endptr==id_buf; *endptr is '\0', so empty string parses as valid ID 0
3. Leading whitespace is silently accepted by strtoul

Should check errno == ERANGE, and that endptr != id_buf.

